"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837989","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-20","<p>All existing recipients of support for mortgage interest are being contacted, provided with information and offered loans so do not need to apply. Data on the number of these claimants by region is not available.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-02-20T12:24:37.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837989/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837989/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-06","Support for Mortgage Interest: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in receipt of support for mortgage interest in Wales have applied for the loan scheme scheduled to begin on 6 April 2018.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","127018"
