"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837402","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-08","<p>Decisions on levels of support provided to those who were infected in Wales are for the Welsh Ministers to make. On 1 November 2017 a new scheme to support those infected in Wales was launched.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-02-08T17:26:42.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837402/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837402/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-05","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what financial arrangements his Department has put place with the Welsh Government to support Welsh victims of the contaminated blood scandal.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","126521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837403","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-08","<p>​While the Foreign Secretary has not raised this issue, officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv most recently raised the case of Ahed Tamimi with the Israeli authorities on 7 February.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-02-08T17:52:22.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837403/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837403/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-05","Ahed Tamimi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions has he had with his Israeli counterpart on the case of Ahed Tamimi since  8 January 2018.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","126522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837404","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-08","<p>​Children in Israeli military detention remains a human rights priority for the UK. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv raised the issue with the Israeli authorities most recently on 7 February. Senior officials from the Foreign and Commonwealth Office raised this issue with the Israeli Ambassador to the UK on 8 January. We also raised the issue as part of the UK’s national statement during Israel’s universal periodic review in the UN Human Rights Council.</p><p>We welcome progress made in recent Israeli policy amendments, and remain committed to working with Israel to secure improvements to its practices surrounding children in detention.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-02-08T17:55:29.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837404/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837404/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-05","Israel: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether his Department has made representations to the Government of Israel on the implementation of the recommendations of the UNICEF report, Children in Israeli Military Detention: Observations and Recommendations, published in 2013.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","126523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837405","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-08","<p>​As the architect of the British Government’s first ever Counter-Extremism Strategy, the Prime Minister has reaffirmed this Government’s unwavering commitment to tackling extremism in all its forms. In Israel and the Occupied Palestinian Territories, the UK’s goal is to preserve the viability of the two-state solution and support peace efforts - a lack of progress towards peace can contribute to regional tensions and extremism. To that end, our support is helping to maintain stability, and we are committed to supporting the institutions of a future Palestinian state to ensure it can effectively deliver services and act as a partner for peace with Israel</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-02-08T17:59:19.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837405/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837405/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-05","Palestinians: Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what his steps the Government is taking to tackle extremism in the Palestinian Territories.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","126524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837406","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-02-13","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-02-13T17:19:48.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837406/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837406/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837406/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-05","Prison Service: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, which companies were contracted by his Department to provide training for prison staff in each of the last five years; and how much his Department has paid to each of those companies for such training.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","126525"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837407","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-02-09","<p>This internal report contains in-depth details of the safety and security procedures at HMP Birmingham which, if released, could compromise security arrangements at the establishment. Therefore, disclosure of this report would not be appropriate.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-02-09T17:07:33.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837407/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837407/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837407/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-05","Birmingham Prison: Civil Disorder","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 25 January 2018 to Question 123578, for what reason his Department does not intend to publish the report into the riot at HMP Birmingham in December 2016.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","126526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837408","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-02-13","<p>The reoffending rates for adult females released from custody and starting community orders by index offence between January 2010 and March 2016 can be found in the attached table.</p><p> </p><p>Please note that the index offence categories in the attached tables are the same as the prison population tables, not the community order offence categories in the probation tables, in the offender management statistics.</p><p> </p><p>There are no clear trends for the reoffending rates of women released from prison or starting community orders broken down by index offence categories. Any large fluctuations seen in the data are due to the small number of offenders in the individual three month cohorts.</p><p> </p><p>We plan to set out a strategy for female offenders in due course, to improve outcomes and services for women in both the community and custody.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-02-13T17:11:20.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837408/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837408/answer","Table for PQ 126527.xlsx","Table for PQ 126527.xlsx","Table for PQ126527","Table for PQ126527","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837408/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-05","Reoffenders: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the recidivism rates for female prisoners who received (a) custodial prison sentences and (b) community supervision orders was by offence category as used in his Department's offender management statistics in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","126527"
